metadata.title: Ayres Thrush
aws::graph::propositions: Snow Aeronautical S-1 was the initial prototype with open cockpit.
Snow Aeronautical S-2 was the pre-production version of S-1.
Snow Aeronautical S-2A was the initial production version.
Snow Aeronautical S-2A was powered by Continental engine.
Snow Aeronautical S-2B was an S-2 powered by 450 hp (340 kW) Pratt & Whitney R-985 engine.
Snow Aeronautical S-2C was a refined production version.
Snow Aeronautical S-2C had wingspan increased by 4 feet 6 inches (1.37 m).
Snow Aeronautical S-2C-600 was an S-2C re-engined with Pratt & Whitney R-1340-AN1.
Snow Aeronautical S-2D had 6,000 lb (2,700 kg) take-off weight.
Simpson documented this information in 2005 on page 39.

text:
### Snow Aeronautical
(per Simpson, 2005, p. 39)

S-1
initial prototype with open cockpit.
S-2
pre-production version of S-1  3 built.
S-2A
initial production version, powered by Continental engine  73 built.
S-2B
S-2 powered by 450 hp (340 kW) Pratt & Whitney R-985  19 built.
S-2C
refined production version, wingspan increased 4 feet 6 inches (1.37 m)  214 built.
S-2C-600
S-2C re-engined with Pratt & Whitney R-1340-AN1.
S-2D
6,000 lb (2,700 kg) take-off weight  105 built.
